tic continuation = explicit formula | 6 |\n31\t| Ramanujan-type series / Pade | FAIL | E | Cipolla DIVERGES, Pade gives 1372 mean error | 6 |\n32\t| Resurgent / trans-series | FAIL | E | Non-perturbative sectors ARE zeta zeros | 6 |\n33\t| Borel summation | FAIL | E | NOT APPLICABLE (power-law not factorial) | 6 |\n34\t| Riemann-Siegel analog | FAIL | E | = Lagarias-Odlyzko method | 6 |\n35\t| Zeta zero compression/FMM | FAIL | I | Spectral flatness 0.91, phase catastrophe | 9 |\n36\t| Connes-Weil quadratic form | FAIL | E | Finds zeros but can't sum them fast | 9 |\n37\t| Resummation (Borel/Pade/Shanks/Richardson/Mellin-Barnes) | FAIL | E | GUE statistics prevent partial sum prediction | 10 |\n38\t| FFT acceleration of explicit formula | FAIL | E | Constant factor only, not asymptotic | 7 |\n39\t| Gram points + Riemann-Siegel | PARTIAL | E | O(x^{1/2}*polylog) -- already known best | 8 |\n40\t| Analytic continuation (7 methods) | FAIL | E | Natural boundary at Re=0 | 8 |\n41\t| LLL/PSLQ integer relations | FAIL | I | Coefficients grow as O(n^{1/3}) | 6 |\n42\t| Selberg deconvolution | FAIL | E | 7-64% error, = Legendre sieve | 9 |\n43\t| Higher-order Richardson (orders 2-10) | FAIL | E | Error oscillatory not smooth; condition number explodes; diverges at high orders | 11 |\n44\t| Levin u/t-transform on zero sum | FAIL | E | WORSE than plain for large x; error not alternating | 11 |\n45\t| Weniger delta transform on zero sum | FAIL | E | Same failure; oscillatory error defeats all transforms | 11 |\n46\t| Smoothed explicit formula (psi_k/ln) | FAIL | I | psi(x)/ln(x) loses prime power corrections; error ~10% | 11 |\n47\t| Zero-count scaling analysis | CLOSED | E | N_min scales as x^{0.25-0.37} (power law), not polylog | 11 |\n48\t\n49\t## Algebraic / Number Theory / p-adic\n50\t\n51\t| Approach | Verdict | Mode | Key Finding | Session |\n52\t|----------|---------|------|-------------|---------|\n53\t| CRT/modular construction | FAIL | C | Fundamentally circular | 3,7,9 |\n54\t| Modular CRT for pi(x) | FAIL | E | pi(x) mod m costs same as pi(x) | 4,5,7 |\n55\t| Chebotarev density theorem | FAIL | C | Need p to compute Frob_p | 4 |\n56\t| Artin L-functions | FAIL | E | = Riemann explicit formula | 4 |\n57\t| Elliptic curve point counts | FAIL | C | Can't invert a_p to p | 4 |\n58\t| p-adic counting | FAIL | E | Encode class numbers, not pi(x) | 4 |\n59\t| Modular forms approach | FAIL | C | Euler products need primes | 5 |\n60\t| p-adic interpolation | FAIL | I | Mahler coefficients grow super-exponentially | 8 |\n61\t| p-adic analysis (5 experiments) | FAIL | I | Not q-adically continuous, equidistributed | 10 |\n62\t| Modular forms (7 experiments) | FAIL | C | Encode primes individually not collectively | 10 |\n63\t| Perfectoid tilting | FAIL | E | Tilting preserves complexity | 9 |\n64\t| Prismatic cohomology | FAIL | E | Formula exists but >= O(x^{1/2+eps}) | 9 |\n65\t| Condensed mathematics | FAIL | E | Categorical, not computational | 9 |\n66\t| Geometric Langlands | FAIL | E | Same complexity as explicit formula | 9 |\n67\t| Motivic integration | FAIL | E | Structural obstruction | 9 |\n68\t| Number field algebraic decomposition | FAIL | E | Splitting doesn't reduce total cost | 7 |\n69\t| Iwasawa theory | FAIL | I | lambda,mu invariants give no shortcut | 7 |\n70\t| Cloitre analytic recurrence (2025) | EXISTS | E | Exact but uses zeta evaluation, not competitive | lit |\n71\t| Farey fractions | FAIL | C | Require phi(k) -> factoring | 8 |\n72\t| Arithmetic derivative | FAIL | C | Requires factoring, O(n^{1/4}) | 8 |\n73\t\n74\t## Sieve / Combinatorial / Counting\n75\t\n76\t| Approach | Verdict | Mode | Key Finding | Session |\n77\t|----------|---------|------|-------------|---------|\n78\t| Sieve weights formula | FAIL | I | Parity barrier (Selberg) | 4 |\n79\t| Redheffer/Mertens matrix | FAIL | E | O(x^{2/3}) same as pi(x) | 8 |\n80\t| Wheel factorization | PARTIAL | - | Constant factor only, NOT complexity class | 8 |